JOHANNESBURG - Stephen Koseff is set to vacate his position as CEO of Investec in October. Koseff has been at the helm for four decades. Co-founder Bernard Kantor will also step down as managing director. READ: Reserve Bank's support for Capitec based on inaccurate information: Viceroy The bank says the move is part of its succession plan to put fresh leadership in place. Koseff and Kantor have been hailed for turning the company into an internationally recognised specialist bank and asset manager. eNCA